# Title: Possible Privilege Escalation via Weak Service Permissions
# Author: Teymur Kheirkhabarov
# Date: 2019-10-26
# Level: high
# Description: Detection of sc.exe utility spawning by user with Medium integrity level to change service ImagePath or FailureCommand
# MITRE Tactic: Persistence
# Tags: attack.persistence, attack.privilege-escalation, attack.execution, attack.stealth, attack.t1574.011
# Reference: https://github.com/SigmaHQ/sigma/blob/master/rules/windows/process_creation/proc_creation_win_sc_change_sevice_image_path_by_non_admin.yml

Image="*\\sc.exe" IntegrityLevel IN ("Medium", "S-1-16-8192") (CommandLine="*config*" CommandLine="*binPath*") OR (CommandLine="*failure*" CommandLine="*command*")